originalText.text:
Just wonderful! Unstructured, creative, hands on fun in a warm and welcoming enviroment.  Ms Cindy at Art studio allows you to get messy and flow at your own pace, embracing art of imagination. My daughter loves her class and has made an incredible progress.
All of the teachers we’ve come across during the ready set go program are passionate, committed and great educators. I’d highly recommend Rutgers Community Programs.

originalText.text: Both of our children have attended Rutgers programs for well over a year now and we couldn't be more satisfied. The teachers are wonderful, the physical space is perfect for little learners with creative minds, and my kids love going to their programs. This is a gem in the neighborhood!

originalText.text: Rutgers Community Programs is a hidden gem on the UWS. The art studio is magical and top notch. The teachers are caring and entertaining while patiently helping little humans learn to interact with one another. It's more than just a school- it's a place to flourish. The gym is on site; you don't have to walk across intersections or to the park to exercise those muscles. You are greeted every day at the door by staff who monitor the facility. I look forward to the weekly email showcasing what they learned and how they interacted with each other so you can see progress and reflect with your child about different topics. They also offer valuable speakers and events for families so we can all navigate the New York education system and have fun during these precious years. It speaks volumes about socialization skills when your child wants to play with their friends every day of the week. We are so thankful for finding Rutgers!

originalText.text: Wonderful early childhood program. All of our children have enjoyed the art classes with Ms. Cindy and tell tales every week of what color the playdough is ready for action.  Our middle one loved on my own 2’s program with special projects and to the big gym, the rooftop and the play space. Very warm and welcoming environment for young ones.

originalText.text: Rutgers is a very warm and supportive environment for kids. Kids are allowed to explore, be creative, and be themselves. I am very thankful for Rutgers as my daughter has really been able to come out of her shell and thrive.
